            "subject": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Fix kfilnd threading"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Ian Ziemba",
          "email": "ian.ziemba@hpe.com",
          "date": "2020-09-16 21:28:11.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Chris Horn",
          "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
          "date": "2022-07-27 15:15:06.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Fix transaction double free",
        "message": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Fix transaction double free\n\nOn receiving an eager message, within kfilnd_tn_state_idle(),\nlnet_parse() is called. If matched, lnet_parse() will call back into\nkfilnd_recv() which may try to issue an RMA command. If the RMA\ncommand fails, the transaction will be freed. Then as the stack is\nunwound back to kfilnd_tn_state_idle(), the transaction is incorrectly\naccessed and freed again. To resolve this issue, do not access the\ntransaction again within kfilnd_tn_state_idle() if lnet_parse() was\nsuccessfully.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nHPE-bug-id: LUS-9365\nSigned-off-by: Ian Ziemba <ian.ziemba@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: Id1d0114f900f12288f973d4764dc19751106b62a\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
